# Claude Visual Review Prompt

Use this template to have Claude Code semantically analyze UI screenshots.

## Usage

```bash
# In Claude Code session:
claude "Review the visual diff between baseline and current screenshots"
```

## Prompt Template

---

**Task:** Semantic visual review of {{ project_name }} UI

**Context:** Compare screenshots in `.visual/` directory:
- Baseline: `.visual/baseline/`
- Current: `.visual/current/`
- Diff report: `.visual/results.json`

**Review Checklist:**

### 1. Layout & Structure
- [ ] Component alignment consistent
- [ ] Spacing follows design system
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints correct
- [ ] No overlapping elements

### 2. Typography
- [ ] Font families correct
- [ ] Font sizes consistent
- [ ] Line heights appropriate
- [ ] Text truncation handled

### 3. Colors & Branding
- [ ] Brand colors accurate
- [ ] Contrast ratios accessible (WCAG AA: 4.5:1)
- [ ] Hover/active states visible
- [ ] Dark mode consistency (if applicable)

### 4. Charts & Data Visualization
- [ ] Axes labeled correctly
- [ ] Legend present and accurate
- [ ] Data points readable
- [ ] Tooltips functional
- [ ] Colors distinguishable

### 5. Forms & Inputs
- [ ] Field labels visible
- [ ] Error states clear
- [ ] Focus indicators present
- [ ] Placeholder text appropriate

### 6. Navigation
- [ ] Active state visible
- [ ] Breadcrumbs accurate
- [ ] Mobile menu functional

{% if domain == 'trading' %}
### 7. Trading-Specific
- [ ] Price display precision
- [ ] Order book depth visible
- [ ] Chart timeframe controls
- [ ] Position indicators clear
- [ ] P&L colors (green/red) correct
{% endif %}

{% if domain == 'workflow' %}
### 7. Workflow-Specific
- [ ] Node connections clear
- [ ] Execution status indicators
- [ ] Error badges visible
- [ ] Canvas zoom controls
{% endif %}

{% if domain == 'data' %}
### 7. Data-Specific
- [ ] Table headers sticky
- [ ] Sorting indicators
- [ ] Pagination controls
- [ ] Filter states visible
{% endif %}

